I loved this dish. I used patty pan squash and heirloom zucchini straight from my garden - along with homegrown basil. I used really good aged balsamic vinegar, which I think worked best because of its sweetness and lower acidity. The Parmesan was also aged and finely ground. To make it into a meal, I added some al dente fettuccine and it was PERFECT. If I had some cherry tomatoes handy, they would have been a tasty addition.

